AB  - A decade ago, a new field developed within the realms of International Business Studies, namely International Entrepreneurship. New buzzwords have emerged, notably the concept of ‘born globals’, and have given way to more rigorous analyses of the phenomenon. A defining article in the development of the field has been Benjamin Oviatt and Patricia McDougall's ‘Toward a Theory of International New Ventures’, published in JIBS in 1994 and awarded the JIBS decade award in 2004.
